00014 // \brief Implementation of the TMXkeff class
00015 //
00016 //
00018 //
00019 // TMXkeff
00020 //
00021 // Thomas Frosio, Transmutex, 07/12/2020
00022 //
00024 // Class to compute keff with power iteration method
00026 /*
00027  * The power iteration algorithm allows to find the largest eigenvalue
00028  * of an endomorphism A as A(v) = lv, v eigenvector, l eigenvalue.
00029  * Given a v0 vector being an approximation of v, the following recurrence
00030  * relation is calculated: v[k+1] = A(v[k]) / norm(Av[k]).
00031  * At each iteration, v is multiplied by the A matrix.
00032  */
00033 
